        "subject": "LU-19179 build: remove RHEL7 handling of fscrypt",
        "message": "LU-19179 build: remove RHEL7 handling of fscrypt\n\nWith the removal of RHEL7 we no longer need the LC_IS_ENCRYPTED\nautoconf test so remove it. Rework the autoconf handling for\nfscrypt. We handle the case of a kernel turning off fscrypt and\nthe case of building only the tools for the Linux native client.\n\nChange-Id: Ic5212f297933f63ae362f2f80e632f1bb3674658\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-sec\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63207\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
